472
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:26,150
Addy'll be fine.

473
00:50:26,320 --> 00:50:29,471
- You afraid?
- Damn right! These are bad people.

474
00:50:29,640 --> 00:50:33,030
- I'm not afraid.
- You're too stupid to be scared.

475
00:50:33,200 --> 00:50:35,953
No reason to be scared.
We'll move the weight.

476
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:37,997
We'll get out.

477
00:50:41,120 --> 00:50:42,997
Hurry back.

478
00:51:26,040 --> 00:51:28,554
Your intelligence really shines.

479
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:32,554
Every cop in the world is looking
for you and you lead them to me.

480
00:51:32,720 --> 00:51:36,315
That is brilliant.
Obviously, there's no respect.

481
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:40,951
But your types wouldn't know
anything about respect, would you?

482
00:51:41,120 --> 00:51:46,752
Respect is the foundation of
civilization and working relationships.

483
00:51:46,920 --> 00:51:51,038
No offence, Tony, but you're getting
a little carried away.

484
00:51:52,480 --> 00:51:56,598
Respect is what separates us from
the niggers and the spics.

485
00:51:57,680 --> 00:52:01,753
When I first met you,
you had intelligence and connections.

486
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:06,232
You had potential. So what do you do?

487
00:52:06,400 --> 00:52:10,075
You get mixed up
with this second-rate stick-up man.

488
00:52:10,240 --> 00:52:12,800
Tony, we just came to do a deal.

489
00:52:19,640 --> 00:52:21,278
What are you selling?

490
00:52:21,440 --> 00:52:23,078
Look, man...

491
00:52:24,080 --> 00:52:26,150
Come on, Tony.

492
00:52:33,120 --> 00:52:35,156
It's taking them a long time.

493
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:40,792
- How stupid do you think I am?
- I don't know what you're thinking.

494
00:52:40,960 --> 00:52:44,953
- We just came here to do a deal.
- Deal?!

495
00:52:47,280 --> 00:52:50,989
I've got thirty keys of primo stuff.
Over a million in street value.

496
00:52:51,160 --> 00:52:53,390
You can have it for half.

497
00:52:53,560 --> 00:52:56,597
- How do you know me?
- I met you through Eddie Grillo.

498
00:52:56,760 --> 00:53:00,275
- Correct. And how did I know him?
- You guys did business.

499
00:53:00,440 --> 00:53:04,035
- Correct. What kind of business?
- You bought from him.

500
00:53:04,200 --> 00:53:05,918
Incorrect!

501
00:53:06,080 --> 00:53:08,878
Eddie Grillo worked for me!

502
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:14,795
These drugs belong to me!
Do you think I'm going to pay you?

503
00:53:14,960 --> 00:53:20,478
Do you think you could come in here,
you son of a bitch, and rip me off?!

504
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:24,235
- No. I didn't know it was yours.
- Jesus Christ.

505
00:53:24,400 --> 00:53:28,109
It doesn't matter what you knew!
What matters is how it looks!

506
00:53:28,280 --> 00:53:31,590
And it looks like you stole from me!

507
00:53:34,480 --> 00:53:37,119
Can you give me a break here?

508
00:53:38,080 --> 00:53:42,119
- Please, Tony.
- Sorry, kid.

509
00:53:42,280 --> 00:53:47,718
We would never have taken this shit
if we'd known it was yours.

510
00:53:47,880 --> 00:53:50,758
We've got all of it right here.

511
00:53:50,920 --> 00:53:53,480
We'd never have taken
these drugs from you.

512
00:53:53,640 --> 00:53:55,676
We've got everything right here.

513
00:53:55,840 --> 00:53:58,229
I can't die like this.

514
00:54:01,360 --> 00:54:03,999
What the fuck are you doing?

515
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:08,597
This is 10, 15 grand. Where's the rest?
Where's the rest?

516
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:12,469
Was I disrespectful, Tony?
Where the fuck is the rest, Tony?

517
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:15,154
- Where's the rest?
- He's fucking lying!

518
00:54:15,320 --> 00:54:19,438
- Let's get the fuck out of here.
- Cue Tip was my best friend, fucker.

519
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:21,830
Come on, Curtis.

520
00:54:45,200 --> 00:54:47,668
- How did it go?
- Get in the car.

521
00:54:47,840 --> 00:54:49,592
What happened, Curtis?

522
00:54:56,680 --> 00:54:58,989
You killed Tony Vago, Raymond?

523
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:03,278
Eddie worked for Vago.
He wanted to kill us in there.

524
00:55:03,440 --> 00:55:06,512
- Would that make you happy?
- No.

525
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:10,394
I thought you knew what you were doing.

526
00:55:16,880 --> 00:55:20,077
Massacre in Vegas. Five dead.
One of them was Tony Vago.

527
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:24,870
- He had half his face burned off.
- And the reason you're telling me this?

528
00:55:25,040 --> 00:55:28,874
Witnesses' descriptions match our guys.
They're driving a Dodge.

529
00:55:29,040 --> 00:55:33,477
Call Richard Pearson at the FBI.
Tell him we'll be there in the morning.

530
00:55:51,680 --> 00:55:55,070
- May I have your attention?
- Who the hell are you?

531
00:55:55,240 --> 00:55:57,390
Who I am is of no importance.

532
00:55:57,560 --> 00:56:01,872
I have been sent here
by Mr Giannino and his associates -

533
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:05,999
- to deal with the situation
that occurred here last evening.

534
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:09,516
- We worked for Mr Vago.
- Mr Vago worked for Mr Giannino.

535
00:56:09,680 --> 00:56:12,592
- So? What do we call you?
- Sir.

536
00:56:13,640 --> 00:56:16,359
You may call me sir.

537
00:56:20,600 --> 00:56:25,230
<i>That high pressure continues</i>
<i>giving us dry days and chilly nights.</i>

538
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:45,917
- Raymond? What are you doing here?
- Nice to see you too, Wayne.

539
00:56:57,120 --> 00:56:59,350
Shit.

540
00:57:29,360 --> 00:57:32,193
Curtis!

541
00:58:02,040 --> 00:58:04,952
I'm sorry I had to come here.
I had no choice.

542
00:58:05,120 --> 00:58:07,588
What happened? This isn't your style.

543
00:58:08,240 --> 00:58:09,878
I don't know.

544
00:58:10,040 --> 00:58:14,556
Curtis went crazy in Grillo's office.
Nobody was supposed to be there.

545
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:17,598
You should never have hooked up
with that asshole.

546
00:58:17,760 --> 00:58:21,594
I don't need a fucking lecture, Wayne.

547
00:58:21,760 --> 00:58:24,638
- I need your help.
- I'm not getting involved.

548
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:30,397
- Remember Cecil in New Mexico?
- I'm not getting involved in this shit.

549
00:58:30,560 --> 00:58:33,870
If anyone saw you,
my parole is down the toilet.

550
00:58:34,040 --> 00:58:36,395
Nobody saw anything.

551
00:58:36,560 --> 00:58:39,552
I need you to make
one phone call for me.

552
00:58:39,720 --> 00:58:41,870
Can you do that?

553
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:47,872
All right, Ray.
One phone call. That's it.

554
00:58:56,320 --> 00:58:59,949
- Can I trust this guy?
- How should I know?

555
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:03,317
You thought you could trust Vago.

556
00:59:17,200 --> 00:59:19,873
The price is the price.

557
00:59:20,040 --> 00:59:24,431
I'll call you tomorrow and tell you
where we're going to meet.

558
00:59:29,040 --> 00:59:31,031
Just make this deal and go.

559
00:59:31,200 --> 00:59:34,875
You hit Tony Vago.
They'll never stop looking for you.

560
00:59:39,240 --> 00:59:42,232
- What are you doing?
- Going to my girlfriend's.

561
00:59:42,400 --> 00:59:45,551
If anyone saw you,
I'll tell the cops you broke in.

562
00:59:45,720 --> 00:59:49,269
- I want you guys gone by tonight.
- Okay, Wayne.

563
00:59:50,120 --> 00:59:53,476
Hey, Wayne? I need your car.

564
00:59:54,120 --> 00:59:58,875
This is fucking unbelievable, man!
You come and take over my house, -

565
00:59:59,040 --> 01:00:03,192
- use my car...
You want to come and fuck my girlfriend?

566
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:12,159
Thanks a lot.

567
01:00:27,120 --> 01:00:29,634
What do you think Vago's people will do?

568
01:00:29,800 --> 01:00:32,598
They don't shit
without permission from Giannino.

569
01:00:33,080 --> 01:00:38,916
Giannino's big on vendettas.
There's no way he'll sit still for this.

570
01:00:39,080 --> 01:00:42,277
- If they find them first...
- We'll pick up body parts.

571
01:00:42,440 --> 01:00:46,399
Can you get me surveillance
on Giannino's shooters?

572
01:00:51,800 --> 01:00:54,234
Are you still mad at me?

573
01:00:56,280 --> 01:00:58,589
Yeah.

574
01:01:01,120 --> 01:01:03,350
Why?

575
01:01:08,240 --> 01:01:12,677
Because you knew that Vago killed
Curtis' best friend, -

576
01:01:12,840 --> 01:01:16,719
- and you still took that lunatic
in there with you.

577
01:01:22,800 --> 01:01:25,268
I know it was stupid.

578
01:01:26,840 --> 01:01:29,593
But it turned out lucky.

579
01:01:33,400 --> 01:01:37,757
It's not enough we've got
every cop in the country looking for us.

580
01:01:37,920 --> 01:01:44,758
Now we have the mob after us too.
We're just blessed with good fortune.

581
01:01:49,560 --> 01:01:51,790
I'm sorry, Addy.

582
01:01:52,760 --> 01:01:56,196
Right now, sorry isn't good enough.

583
01:02:32,480 --> 01:02:37,474
<i>With the lioness out of the way,</i>
<i>the hyenas bring the wildebeest down.</i>

584
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:51,355
Do you like guns?

585
01:02:51,520 --> 01:02:56,435
I've been to the firing range a lot,
but I've never seen one like that.

586
01:02:56,600 --> 01:02:58,591
Sig 9 millimetre.

587
01:02:58,760 --> 01:03:02,992
You get hit with that puppy,
you'd be lucky only to lose a limb.

588
01:03:15,280 --> 01:03:19,876
At the rest stop, you were trying to
get us away, weren't you?

589
01:03:23,920 --> 01:03:27,595
When this whole thing started,
I was so scared.

590
01:03:28,320 --> 01:03:30,754
Now I just feel numb.

591
01:03:31,360 --> 01:03:36,514
If you need to be scared, you should
be scared about your boyfriend.

592
01:03:44,480 --> 01:03:46,232
Put it down, Gordon!

593
01:03:46,400 --> 01:03:49,437
Jesus Christ. It's cool.

594
01:03:49,600 --> 01:03:51,795
It's not even loaded.

595
01:03:51,960 --> 01:03:55,475
You know how close you came
to getting killed?

596
01:03:56,640 --> 01:04:00,713
You two morons get ready.
We're going to make a food run.

597
01:04:01,760 --> 01:04:04,513
Pack up. I'm going for food.

598
01:04:09,400 --> 01:04:11,755
Marcus. Help me load up the stuff.

599
01:04:19,160 --> 01:04:21,515
What?

600
01:04:23,960 --> 01:04:28,351
You have a problem because I'm
listening to Curtis' point of view?

601
01:04:28,520 --> 01:04:31,353
His point of view?

602
01:04:31,520 --> 01:04:36,071
What point of view? He is psychotic.
Would you please stop imitating him?

603
01:04:36,240 --> 01:04:39,789
I'm not imitating him.
I don't condone what they're doing.

604
01:04:39,960 --> 01:04:44,476
I'm just trying to understand
why it is they do it.

605
01:04:46,040 --> 01:04:49,430
- What's happening to you?
- This is a game.

606
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:52,592
Everyone who plays the game
knows the rules.

607
01:04:52,760 --> 01:04:54,318
The cops are the good guys.

608
01:04:54,480 --> 01:04:58,951
The good guys' job is to catch them.
The bad guys' job is to not get caught.

609
01:05:00,680 --> 01:05:05,549
- Just get away from me, please.
- We have to get something to eat.

610
01:05:27,800 --> 01:05:30,314
Where are you going, Donna?

611
01:05:30,480 --> 01:05:32,755
To take a bath.

612
01:05:44,680 --> 01:05:47,672
- A shot of Scotch.
- Coming up, darling.

613
01:05:50,200 --> 01:05:53,397
- How much further to where we're going?
- Why?

614
01:05:53,560 --> 01:05:55,869
- Just curious.
- Stay curious.

615
01:05:56,040 --> 01:06:00,431
- I don't know about Mexico.
- You'll have a good time.

616
01:06:00,600 --> 01:06:05,594
- It's easy for you. You've got Addy.
- You'll meet somebody.

617
01:06:05,760 --> 01:06:10,311
Addy knows people.
She's got a friend down there, some guy.

618
01:06:10,480 --> 01:06:15,190
He knows some chick named Juanita.
Addy says she's going to introduce you.

619
01:06:15,360 --> 01:06:18,432
- I don't get set up.
- What are you talking about?

620
01:06:18,600 --> 01:06:21,990
- About getting set up. I'm not with it.
- Why not?

621
01:06:22,160 --> 01:06:25,755
- What did Addy say about this girl?
- She said she was very sweet.

622
01:06:27,400 --> 01:06:31,154
- Nice personality, right?
- She has a terrific personality.

623
01:06:31,320 --> 01:06:34,551
- What does she look like?
- What difference does it make?

624
01:06:34,720 --> 01:06:38,599
- Go right in there. Forget about it.
- No, I don't even walk that way.

625
01:06:38,760 --> 01:06:43,117
Every time somebody tells me about
a girl's personality before her looks, -

626
01:06:43,280 --> 01:06:45,032
- I know she'll be butt-ugly.

627
01:06:45,200 --> 01:06:48,272
- How do you know that?
- I've been through it.

628
01:06:48,440 --> 01:06:54,675
Three months ago, my cousin set me up.
This girl's supposed to have a big ass.

629
01:06:54,840 --> 01:06:56,478
So I'm like cool.

630
01:06:56,640 --> 01:07:00,235
An hour later, I'm at the Beef Basket.

631
01:07:00,400 --> 01:07:03,949
I kick back, you know,
in a booth. Chilling.

632
01:07:04,120 --> 01:07:09,114
And in walks the butt-ugliest woman
I've ever seen in my life.

633
01:07:09,280 --> 01:07:13,034
She walks over to the table and smiles.
The bitch has five teeth.

634
01:07:13,200 --> 01:07:15,395
- That's cold.
- Brutal.

635
01:07:15,560 --> 01:07:18,870
You know what she orders? Ribs.

636
01:07:19,040 --> 01:07:22,396
The bitch has five teeth
and she's chewing on a rib.

637
01:07:22,560 --> 01:07:25,996
Chewing's not even the right word.
The bitch was gumming it!

638
01:07:26,160 --> 01:07:30,597
That's when I just said:
"Fuck it. I've had enough of this.

639
01:07:30,760 --> 01:07:35,151
I'm not spending
one more minute with this ugly, -

640
01:07:35,320 --> 01:07:38,756
- sabre-toothed-tiger-looking,
gum-smacking bitch."

641
01:07:38,920 --> 01:07:42,390
So I got up, went to the bathroom,
climbed out the window -

642
01:07:42,560 --> 01:07:44,630
- and booked to the pad.

643
01:07:44,800 --> 01:07:48,918
So when Addy's talking about
hooking me up with some great girl, -

644
01:07:49,080 --> 01:07:55,235
- there's no way in the fucking world
that's going to happen to the dog.

645
01:07:57,200 --> 01:08:01,432
She could've been a wonderful girl
with a fantastic personality.

646
01:08:01,600 --> 01:08:03,750
Yeah, right.

647
01:08:10,880 --> 01:08:14,668
- You eat a lot of that stuff.
- I'm pregnant.

648
01:08:16,440 --> 01:08:19,796
- How long have you known?
- A couple of days.

649
01:08:20,440 --> 01:08:23,637
- Raymond know?
- No.

650
01:08:23,800 --> 01:08:27,315
- You're not going to tell him?
- Yeah, I'll tell him.

651
01:08:27,960 --> 01:08:29,598
When?

652
01:08:30,160 --> 01:08:33,436
When the time is right.
He's got too much on his mind.

653
01:08:34,480 --> 01:08:37,153
You should give him a chance
to think about it.

654
01:08:37,320 --> 01:08:41,598
- We'll go to Mexico and live there.
- That's a dream, Addy.

655
01:08:44,320 --> 01:08:46,754
That's real.

656
01:08:46,920 --> 01:08:50,629
If Raymond says we'll do that,
that's what we'll do.

657
01:08:50,800 --> 01:08:54,509
Go to Mexico, buy a house by the ocean
and be a family.

658
01:08:58,520 --> 01:09:01,876
What about you and Gordon?
Do you love him?

659
01:09:03,560 --> 01:09:05,516
You think you know someone, -

660
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:10,196
- that there might be
something to build on...

661
01:09:10,360 --> 01:09:13,875
Then you see a side of him
you never knew existed.

662
01:09:23,680 --> 01:09:25,671
Howdy, Tex.

663
01:09:26,680 --> 01:09:29,797
- What's your problem, man?
- Right now it's you.

664
01:09:29,960 --> 01:09:32,599
- You bumped into me.
- We don't have time for this.

665
01:09:32,760 --> 01:09:35,115
We've got time.

666
01:09:39,080 --> 01:09:41,548
Come on, Gordon. Kick his ass!

667
01:09:41,720 --> 01:09:43,950
Shit.

668
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:46,031
That's enough, Curtis. End it.

669
01:09:46,200 --> 01:09:48,589
I've got it.

670
01:09:51,320 --> 01:09:53,515
Jesus Christ, Gordon!

671
01:09:54,360 --> 01:09:57,113
Get the fuck back to the car!

672
01:09:59,000 --> 01:10:01,878
- I need a doctor.
- No, you don't.

673
01:10:08,840 --> 01:10:12,799
- Is he dead?
- Yes. Move! Get in the car!

674
01:10:27,520 --> 01:10:30,637
Jesus, that was the most insane move
I've ever seen.

675
01:10:30,800 --> 01:10:33,792
You killed a guy over some pizza?

676
01:10:33,960 --> 01:10:38,397
How does it feel, Gordon?
To throw your life down the toilet.

677
01:10:38,560 --> 01:10:41,472
- It was self-defence.
- That's not self-defence.

678
01:10:41,640 --> 01:10:47,875
Self-defence is: I hit you, you hit me.
Not: I hit you, you kill me!

679
01:10:48,320 --> 01:10:51,039
Idiot. Fucking idiot.

680
01:11:02,720 --> 01:11:05,598
- What happened?
- Gordon killed somebody.

681
01:11:05,760 --> 01:11:08,115
Get some ice. We're in a rush.

682
01:11:08,280 --> 01:11:12,353
You're supposed to be the leader.
You can't even control Gordon now.

683
01:11:14,480 --> 01:11:16,835
Gordon?

684
01:11:17,000 --> 01:11:21,630
It happened so fast.
Would you just get some ice, please?

685
01:12:44,920 --> 01:12:48,959
Hello.
I hope we didn't frighten you, Wayne.

686
01:12:49,120 --> 01:12:51,998
- It <i>is</i> Wayne, isn't it?
- Who the hell are you?

687
01:12:57,320 --> 01:13:03,395
I love that look.
No matter how often I do this.

688
01:13:03,560 --> 01:13:07,269
That "I'm-in-deep-doo-doo-now" look.

689
01:13:07,760 --> 01:13:10,320
- What do you want?
- To the point. Good.

690
01:13:10,480 --> 01:13:15,793
It saves everybody time and energy.
I just want to know where Raymond went.

691
01:13:15,960 --> 01:13:17,951
Raymond who?

692
01:13:19,840 --> 01:13:22,559
You were doing so well up till now.

693
01:13:22,720 --> 01:13:26,156
You were direct, to the point,
made eye contact.

694
01:13:26,320 --> 01:13:29,153
- Do I look stupid to you, Wayne?
- No.

695
01:13:29,320 --> 01:13:32,437
Then you must know that I refer to
Mr Raymond Lembecke.

696
01:13:32,600 --> 01:13:36,354
Your former cell mate. The gentleman
who was here earlier today.

697
01:13:36,520 --> 01:13:39,159
I spent last night with my girlfriend.

698
01:13:39,320 --> 01:13:42,949
Somebody broke in through my window.
I don't know who it...

699
01:13:43,120 --> 01:13:44,838
Just a minute.

700
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:48,754
You spent the night at your girlfriend's
and you're just coming home?

701
01:13:48,920 --> 01:13:53,357
Then how did you know
that someone broke into your house?

702
01:13:53,520 --> 01:13:57,559
- I saw the broken glass.
- Look at me.

703
01:13:59,360 --> 01:14:02,591
You're lying. You know you're lying.

704
01:14:02,760 --> 01:14:05,320
I know you're lying.
They know you're lying.

705
01:14:05,480 --> 01:14:08,597
I haven't seen Raymond
since I got out of prison.

706
01:14:09,520 --> 01:14:15,311
I always give a man a decent chance.
Usually it's three wrong answers.

707
01:14:15,880 --> 01:14:19,429
If you make a guy tell you
what you want to know right away, -

708
01:14:19,600 --> 01:14:21,875
- it robs him of his dignity.

709
01:14:22,040 --> 01:14:24,508
He feels he didn't even try
to be a stand-up guy.

710
01:14:24,680 --> 01:14:29,151
- I'm telling you that I haven't...
- You're telling me nothing.

711
01:14:29,320 --> 01:14:32,710
But you will tell me
what I want to know.

712
01:14:32,880 --> 01:14:38,637
I only mention it, because everybody
tells me what I want to know eventually.

713
01:14:40,760 --> 01:14:43,115
Please sit down, Wayne.

714
01:14:44,360 --> 01:14:47,033
I say again, take a seat.

715
01:15:02,160 --> 01:15:03,798
Where are we going, Ray?

716
01:15:03,960 --> 01:15:07,032
I'm going to do the deal
at my brother's house.

717
01:15:07,200 --> 01:15:09,634
He's away in Canada.

718
01:15:42,560 --> 01:15:46,917
You're doing very well, son.
Now, where in New Mexico?

719
01:15:48,000 --> 01:15:52,039
- Where in New Mexico?
- I swear to God, I don't know!

720
01:15:53,560 --> 01:15:56,313
He just said New Mexico.

721
01:15:57,920 --> 01:16:01,117
Wayne, stay with me, son.

722
01:16:02,760 --> 01:16:06,070
Raymond was raised in New Mexico,
wasn't he?

723
01:16:07,040 --> 01:16:09,952
And he still has family there?

724
01:16:11,200 --> 01:16:14,590
He has a brother.
I don't know where he lives.

725
01:16:17,120 --> 01:16:19,634
Thank you very much, son.

726
01:17:13,120 --> 01:17:15,350
I'll be in in a minute, okay?

727
01:17:30,240 --> 01:17:32,754
I no longer care what happens to me.

728
01:17:32,920 --> 01:17:37,391
I just don't want anything
to happen to Donna, all right?

729
01:18:12,440 --> 01:18:14,078
What's so funny?

730
01:18:14,240 --> 01:18:18,119
Old Gordon over there
just sitting there all teary-eyed.

731
01:18:18,280 --> 01:18:20,919
The fool's never
killed anybody before.

732
01:18:21,080 --> 01:18:24,755
- He still hasn't.
- What are you talking about?

733
01:18:26,600 --> 01:18:28,591
That guy in the parking lot...

734
01:18:28,760 --> 01:18:31,911
He wasn't dead.
He was just hurt real bad.

735
01:18:33,160 --> 01:18:35,754
I had to finish him off.

736
01:18:46,280 --> 01:18:49,238
My whole life I've been afraid.

737
01:18:50,720 --> 01:18:53,234
Now tonight...

738
01:18:56,080 --> 01:18:59,231
I tell myself it was self-defence.

739
01:19:00,600 --> 01:19:02,750
It wasn't.

740
01:19:02,920 --> 01:19:07,914
I could've walked away
before it started. But I didn't.

741
01:19:12,280 --> 01:19:16,637
I just wanted them to know
that I wasn't afraid.

742
01:19:21,040 --> 01:19:23,952
I wanted to impress them.

743
01:19:56,960 --> 01:19:59,474
I love you, Raymond.

744
01:20:14,480 --> 01:20:19,110
If I ever thought
that it could get this bad, I mean...

745
01:20:20,520 --> 01:20:24,308
- I didn't mean it to get this crazy.
- I know. It's okay.

746
01:20:27,560 --> 01:20:30,677
- I love you.
- I love you too.

747
01:20:31,680 --> 01:20:35,753
- Forever?
- I love you more than forever.

748
01:20:36,760 --> 01:20:40,514
Forever'll be done and I'll love you.

749
01:20:41,520 --> 01:20:45,354
You know...
we've been together for a long time.

750
01:20:45,520 --> 01:20:48,876
And us going to Mexico...

751
01:20:49,040 --> 01:20:53,909
That's kind of like saying we'll spend
the rest of our lives together.

752
01:20:54,080 --> 01:20:56,719
Once we get down to Mexico...

753
01:20:56,880 --> 01:20:59,519
...you know, maybe we should...

754
01:20:59,680 --> 01:21:01,557
What?

755
01:21:01,720 --> 01:21:04,439
Once we're there, if you want...

756
01:21:05,200 --> 01:21:07,714
Are you asking me to marry you?

757
01:21:09,480 --> 01:21:12,358
- Yes.
- Really?

758
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:15,673
What do you say?

759
01:21:15,840 --> 01:21:18,035
I say yes.

760
01:21:37,440 --> 01:21:40,398
<i>They're at the brother's house.</i>

761
01:21:40,560 --> 01:21:42,596
Thank you.

762
01:22:23,640 --> 01:22:25,790
- Yeah, Thompson.
- It's Marcus.

763
01:22:25,960 --> 01:22:29,999
- Marcus? Where are you?
<i>- At Raymond's brother's house.</i>

764
01:22:30,160 --> 01:22:34,631
Outside of Truth or Consequences,
about three miles south on highway 25.

765
01:22:34,800 --> 01:22:36,950
- Are the hostages with you?
- Yes.

766
01:22:37,120 --> 01:22:42,274
- It'd be better if you can get away.
- No, I won't abandon these hostages.

767
01:22:42,440 --> 01:22:45,591
Just make sure
your people don't kill us.

768
01:22:45,760 --> 01:22:49,309
Yo, man, just take care of that for me!

769
01:22:52,280 --> 01:22:54,589
- What are you doing?
- I made a phone call.

770
01:22:55,320 --> 01:22:57,595
- To who?
- To my boy.

771
01:22:58,600 --> 01:23:02,354
- At 4:45 in the morning?
- He works graveyard.

772
01:23:03,040 --> 01:23:05,600
What did you call him for?

773
01:23:05,760 --> 01:23:10,914
- You ask a lot of questions, Raymond.
- You're not answering any.

774
01:23:17,000 --> 01:23:22,199
I called him to make sure
everything was okay with my mother.

775
01:23:23,040 --> 01:23:27,875
She's on welfare. I've not exactly
been in a position to check up on her.

776
01:23:29,200 --> 01:23:33,796
- Why didn't you call her?
- First of all, she's sleeping.

777
01:23:33,960 --> 01:23:37,919
Second, even if something <i>was</i> wrong,
she wouldn't tell me.

778
01:23:38,080 --> 01:23:42,232
She wouldn't tell me.
She's like that. She's proud.

779
01:23:43,080 --> 01:23:45,435
I get it.

780
01:23:45,960 --> 01:23:49,236
Call your friend back. Call him back!

781
01:23:50,200 --> 01:23:53,237
When he answers,
all you've got to do is tell him:

782
01:23:53,400 --> 01:23:57,188
"I just want to make sure
you understood what I said."

783
01:24:04,920 --> 01:24:06,876
Let me listen.

784
01:24:08,560 --> 01:24:13,475
- Frankie, it's Marcus.
<i>- Did you fucking forget something?</i>

785
01:24:13,640 --> 01:24:16,279
Did you understand what I told you?

786
01:24:16,440 --> 01:24:20,069
<i>- What do you think I am? Stupid?</i>
- I just wanted to make sure.

787
01:24:20,240 --> 01:24:25,075
<i>I'll go check on your mom in a while.</i>
<i>Mind if I put on a shirt first?</i>

788
01:24:29,400 --> 01:24:32,073
- Thanks, man.
<i>- Yeah, later.</i>

789
01:24:35,400 --> 01:24:37,356
I'm sorry, man.

790
01:24:40,760 --> 01:24:43,228
Everything's fucked up.

791
01:24:54,840 --> 01:24:57,274
We've got them. Assemble the team.

792
01:26:27,400 --> 01:26:29,356
Wake up. We've got to go.

793
01:26:29,520 --> 01:26:32,557
- Go where?
- Mexico, but we've got to go now.

794
01:26:32,720 --> 01:26:37,999
- But we've got to do the deal.
- Fuck the deal. I'm thinking of us.

795
01:26:38,160 --> 01:26:41,789
- There's more to think of than us.
- The others can do what they want.

796
01:26:41,960 --> 01:26:44,394
I'm pregnant, Ray.

797
01:26:45,240 --> 01:26:49,836
- What are you talking about?
- You're going to be a daddy.

798
01:26:50,000 --> 01:26:52,798
Why didn't you tell me before?

799
01:26:53,960 --> 01:26:57,396
I just didn't want you to think
you had to marry me.

800
01:26:57,560 --> 01:27:00,438
Think I had to marry you?

801
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:04,149
I wanted to marry you
the first time I saw you.

802
01:27:13,080 --> 01:27:15,753
Come on. We've got to go.

803
01:27:42,600 --> 01:27:45,751
Look at this piece of shit.
I found him hiding.

804
01:27:45,920 --> 01:27:50,596
Get him in the house, Curtis.
Addy, load the car.

805
01:27:52,680 --> 01:27:54,716
Get in there.

806
01:27:57,480 --> 01:28:00,995
- What's going on?
- Shut up. Listen to me.

807
01:28:02,120 --> 01:28:05,715
Something's going to go down here,
but help is on the way.

808
01:28:05,880 --> 01:28:11,113
If anything happens before help arrives,
you grab Donna and get her out of here.

809
01:28:11,280 --> 01:28:14,795
I'm a drug enforcement agent.
You never killed that guy.

810
01:28:14,960 --> 01:28:18,953
When Curtis went over to him,
he was still alive.

811
01:28:23,040 --> 01:28:27,716
- Why didn't you tell us before?
- I couldn't trust you. Just stay down.

812
01:28:33,000 --> 01:28:34,911
Hurry up, Addy.

813
01:28:41,400 --> 01:28:45,632
- Just do the deal, Ray.
- I'm going to do the deal.

814
01:29:01,240 --> 01:29:03,674
You Raymond Lembecke?

815
01:29:04,560 --> 01:29:08,633
- That's right.
- I'm Cecil. What have you got?

816
01:29:08,920 --> 01:29:11,229
Come inside.

817
01:29:24,440 --> 01:29:27,512
You don't know who you're fucking with.

818
01:29:28,480 --> 01:29:30,436
Shut up.

819
01:29:35,280 --> 01:29:37,635
That looks like it hurts.

820
01:29:38,880 --> 01:29:41,348
This is my lucky quarter.

821
01:29:45,280 --> 01:29:47,396
You'd better get one of these.

822
01:29:49,600 --> 01:29:52,478
You don't look that lucky.

823
01:30:03,560 --> 01:30:06,313
- We're going to have to test it.
- Take one.

824
01:30:27,880 --> 01:30:31,395
- You seem a little too nervous, man.
- I'm in a hurry.

825
01:30:58,080 --> 01:31:00,116
It's good.

826
01:31:05,960 --> 01:31:08,713
You're a rich man now.
What're you going to do?

827
01:31:08,880 --> 01:31:11,269
None of your business.

828
01:31:21,000 --> 01:31:23,798
Jesus Christ, look at that!

829
01:31:28,720 --> 01:31:29,789
Shit!

830
01:31:43,520 --> 01:31:45,112
Come on!

831
01:32:23,600 --> 01:32:26,353
Drop the weapon!

832
01:32:34,200 --> 01:32:36,156
Go. Stay low.

833
01:32:41,600 --> 01:32:44,353
Gordon, Donna, follow me!

834
01:32:44,520 --> 01:32:46,590
Come on, honey!

835
01:32:59,360 --> 01:33:01,078
We'll be okay.

836
01:33:04,040 --> 01:33:05,951
It's going to be all right.

837
01:33:25,720 --> 01:33:27,472
Stay down.

838
01:33:32,520 --> 01:33:34,431
Gordon! Get down!

839
01:33:53,800 --> 01:33:55,950
Gordon!

840
01:34:04,880 --> 01:34:08,031
- No, I'm not one of them.
- I know.

841
01:34:08,800 --> 01:34:11,792
- Please don't.
- Close your eyes.

842
01:34:56,440 --> 01:34:58,476
Snipers! Verify your targets!

843
01:34:58,640 --> 01:35:00,392
Target verified.

844
01:35:00,560 --> 01:35:02,357
Go, go, go, now!

845
01:35:10,560 --> 01:35:12,471
Give me the gun, Addy.

846
01:35:12,640 --> 01:35:14,835
Give me the gun.

847
01:35:20,960 --> 01:35:23,030
Oh, honey...

848
01:35:34,400 --> 01:35:36,470
Come on.

849
01:35:40,600 --> 01:35:42,830
You're okay.

850
01:35:50,800 --> 01:35:53,109
Hold your fire!

851
01:35:56,720 --> 01:35:59,234
It's going to be okay.

852
01:36:00,040 --> 01:36:02,156
On me!

853
01:36:10,120 --> 01:36:11,997
Raymond!

854
01:36:14,920 --> 01:36:17,275
Raymond, stop!

855
01:36:18,520 --> 01:36:21,432
Stop, goddamn it! Drop it!

856
01:36:23,000 --> 01:36:25,912
I'm a drug enforcement agent!

857
01:36:37,120 --> 01:36:40,874
- I just want to be alone with Addy.
- It's over, man.

858
01:42:28,200 --> 01:42:29,792
